Schools are dropping the Holocaust from history lessons to avoid offending Muslim pupils, a government backed study has revealed. 

It found some teachers are reluctant to cover the atrocity for fear of upsetting students whose beliefs include Holocaust denial. 

There is also resistance to tackling the 11th century Crusades - where Christians fought Muslim armies for control of Jerusalem - because lessons often contradict what is taught in local mosques.

"Civilizations die from suicide, not murder," wrote Arnold Toynbee in his now mostly forgotten work on the subject.
----------------------------------
Take a look at Europe. They are bound on destroying themselves. So is Canada, and even USA has its own discernible tendencies toward committing suicide. Why? Is that the logical ending for a democracy?
Do we need a dictatorship to instill the sense of purpose? To shake off the ultimate hedonism we are drowning in?
Totalitarian societies all started as socialist movements (Hitler, Stalin, Pol Pot). Is this a precursor to destruction? Does it have to go in cycles?
